However, since we don't have any direct measure of distance covered or speed, calculating the actual jogging speed remains challenging based solely on the provided data.


We also notice that the low-passed acceleration data appears relatively stable compared to raw accelerations, suggesting effective reduction of unwanted signals like gravity.

